<paragraph blockId="62.[178,1086,389,616]" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">
R e c o g n i t i o n: The female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2015" box="[588,691,389,411]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="snizeki">
<emphasis box="[588,691,389,411]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">A. snizeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a dorsally black gaster, without metallic shine. The episternal sulcus extends to the anteroventral margin of the mesopleuron and the arolia are present. Additionally, the clypeus, the frons, the vertex and the pronotal collar are impunctate. The female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2015" box="[820,920,477,498]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="snizeki">
<emphasis box="[820,920,477,498]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">A. snizeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. SMITH" authorityYear="1856" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">A. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in being smaller (
<quantity box="[581,678,506,528]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" unit="mm" value="18.5">18.5 mm</quantity>
) and having the frons and the vertex impunctate (
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. SMITH" authorityYear="1856" box="[313,429,536,557]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis box="[313,429,536,557]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">A. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a bodylength of 
<quantity box="[681,793,536,558]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.3" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" unit="mm" value="29.5" valueMax="33.0" valueMin="26.0">26-33 mm</quantity>
and frons and vertex are punctate). The female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2015" box="[436,534,565,586]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="snizeki">
<emphasis box="[436,534,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">A. snizeki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="SPINOLA" authorityYear="1839" box="[670,785,565,586]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubripes">
<emphasis box="[670,785,565,586]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">A. rubripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a characteristically shaped clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[346,420,594,616]" captionStart="Figs 21-25" captionStartId="76.[178,218,870,892]" captionTargetBox="[178,697,218,854]" captionTargetId="figure-1@76.[178,708,212,861]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figs 21-25: clypeus of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280423/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) (Clypeus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="SPINOLA" authorityYear="1839" box="[559,673,594,616]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubripes">
<emphasis box="[559,673,594,616]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">A. rubripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<figureCitation box="[717,793,594,616]" captionStart="Figs 38-43" captionStartId="77.[178,218,1566,1588]" captionTargetBox="[178,752,922,1556]" captionTargetId="figure-10@77.[178,752,922,1556]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Figs 38-43: clypeus of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5292833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5292833/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[178,1086,631,741]" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">D e s c r i p t i o n: Gaster dorsally black, without metallic shine, pruinose. Episternal sulcus extends to anteroventral margin of mesopleuron, supra-antennal lamellate projection absent, mesopleural venter not produced anteriorly, arolia present and claws have no basal tooth.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[178,1086,756,1130]" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">
<specimenCount box="[178,199,762,783]" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: 
<quantity box="[220,319,756,778]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="62" pageNumber="369" unit="mm" value="18.5">18.5 mm</quantity>
. Black, with following reddish-brown: mandible (except apex), scape, pedicel, flagellomeres I-III (remaining flagellomeres brownish ventrally), pronotal collar dorsally and laterally, pronotal lobe, tegula, foreleg, midlegs (except femur dorsally), hindleg (dorsally darkened) and petiole ventrally. Wings hyaline. Clypeus, frons, gena, pronotal lobe and propodeum posterolaterally covered with appressed silvery setae; remaining parts of thorax and propodeum covered with fine, sparse appressed setae. Erect setae whitish. Clypeus elongate, with truncate median lobe, lateral tooth distinct, lateral sides slightly concave (
<figureCitation box="[484,560,961,984]" captionStart="Figs 21-25" captionStartId="76.[178,218,870,892]" captionTargetBox="[178,697,218,854]" captionTargetId="figure-1@76.[178,708,212,861]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="Figs 21-25: clypeus of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280423" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280423/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
), disk distinctly convex (
<figureCitation box="[815,891,961,983]" captionStart="Figs 47-64" captionStartId="78.[178,218,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[186,806,794,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-9@78.[178,806,794,1571]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="Figs 47-64: clypeus of female in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5292839" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5292839/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Frons, vertex and pronotal collar impunctate. Scutum transversely striate, without distinct punctures; scutellum longitudinally striate; metanotum irregularly structured. Propodeal enclosure transversely striate. Mesopleuron, and mesopleural venter transversely striate, metapleuron and propodeum laterally punctato-rugose. Pronotal collar dorsally: 
<figureCitation box="[988,1081,1079,1101]" captionStart="Figs 130-135" captionStartId="83.[178,218,1574,1596]" captionTargetBox="[178,646,907,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-14@83.[178,646,907,1564]" captionTargetPageId="83" captionText="Figs 130-135: pronotal collar of female in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297278/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">Fig. 132</figureCitation>
, laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[275,349,1108,1130]" captionStart="Figs 95-100" captionStartId="80.[178,218,1575,1597]" captionTargetBox="[178,675,908,1564]" captionTargetId="figure-14@80.[178,675,908,1565]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="Figs 95-100: pronotal collar of female in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5292845" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5292845/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="369">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
. Flagellomere I:II=1.6; length of petiole = hindtarsomeres I+II.
</paragraph>
